---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { termsAlternates } from '../../../lib/seo';

const appName = 'MarkNote';
const appIcon = '/app-icons/marknote.png';
const title = `${appName} Terms of Service`;
const description =
  'Terms of Service for MarkNote, the KokomaSoft local-first Markdown editing and preview web service.';
---

<Layout
  lang="en"
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/en/terms/marknote/"
  alternates={termsAlternates('marknote')}
  xDefaultPath="/ko/terms/marknote/"
  image={appIcon}
  favicon={appIcon}
  headerBrandName={appName}
  headerIcon={appIcon}
  headerHref="https://md.kokomasoft.com/"
  ogType="article"
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-brand">
        <img src={appIcon} alt="MarkNote app icon" width="76" height="76" />
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">MarkNote Legal</p>
          <h1>MarkNote Terms of Service</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: May 21, 2026</p>
      <p class="intro">
        These Terms of Service govern your use of MarkNote (the "Service"), a Markdown editing and
        preview web service provided by KokomaSoft. By using the Service, you agree to these terms
        and any additional notices shown within the Service. If you do not agree, please stop using
        the Service.
      </p>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Service Overview</h2>
        <p>
          MarkNote is a local-first Markdown editor that runs in your browser. It provides document
          editing and preview, file and folder management, and optional Google Drive integration for
          editing files. Available features may vary by browser environment, region, and connection
          status.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Fees</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is currently provided free of charge. If paid features are introduced in the
          future, we will give prior notice and apply separate terms.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Your Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>
          You are responsible for the content you create, upload, save, or share through the Service,
          and you must hold all rights and permissions required for that content. You must not use the
          Service in violation of laws, third-party rights, or platform policies. We recommend backing
          up important documents separately.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Local Data Storage</h2>
        <p>
          Documents in app work folders are stored in browser storage (OPFS), temporary drafts in
          IndexedDB, and app settings in localStorage — all on your own device. Document bodies and
          file paths are not transmitted to operator servers. Clearing your browser's site data
          removes this local data.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Google Drive Integration (Optional)</h2>
        <p>
          Google Drive integration is optional, and local editing works without a Google account.
          When connected, the Service uses Google authorization and the Google Drive API to read and
          save the Drive files you choose directly. Your use of your Google account and Drive is
          subject to Google's terms and policies, and the Service's handling of Google user data
          adheres to the
          <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
          including the Limited Use requirements. For details on data handling, see the
          <a href="/en/privacy/marknote/">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Intellectual Property and Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          You retain the rights to the documents you create. Rights to the Service's trademarks,
          design, and source code belong to KokomaSoft or the respective owners, and open-source
          components are governed by their respective licenses (MIT, etc.).
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is provided "AS IS" without warranties of fitness for a particular purpose,
          uninterrupted availability, error-free operation, or no data loss. You use the Service at
          your own risk.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the extent permitted by applicable law, KokomaSoft is not liable for any direct,
          indirect, incidental, or consequential damages (including data loss) arising from use or
          inability to use the Service.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Changes and Discontinuation</h2>
        <p>
          KokomaSoft may modify or discontinue all or part of the Service with prior notice. If there
          are changes to features, data handling, or external components, we will update these terms
          or the Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>When these terms change, we will update the last-updated date on this page.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These terms are interpreted and applied under the laws of the Republic of Korea.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-section">
        <h2>12. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Contact: <a href="mailto:kueen108@gmail.com">kueen108@gmail.com</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .legal-page .container {
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }

  .legal-brand {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-brand img {
    width: 76px;
    height: 76px;
    border-radius: 18px;
    box-shadow: 0 16px 36px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.16);
  }

  .legal-brand .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  h1 {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .intro,
  .legal-section p {
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.82;
  }

  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
  }

  .legal-section {
    padding-top: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-section a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .legal-brand {
      align-items: flex-start;
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
